    "Duration: 75 minutes",
    "Note-taker: Priya Patel",
    "",
    "## Pre-Meeting Context",
    "",
    "Three weeks have passed since the November 15 sync where we reviewed the Q4 churn spike. All four leads had action items from that meeting, and this sync was structured as a follow-up review followed by new Q4 close-out discussions. Sarah also wanted to preview the December MRR projection, which is tracking significantly ahead of plan.",
    "",
    "## Action Item Follow-up from Nov 15 Sync",
    "",
    "### AI Copilot Error Rate (Owner: Jake Morrison)",
    "",
    "Jake presented the error rate improvement timeline on the conference room screen. The AI Copilot error rate has moved from 7.2% (production, as of November 15) to 5.8% in staging. The improvement came from three changes deployed together:",
    "",
    "1. Input validation layer: A new pre-processing step that catches unsupported operations before they reach the model. This alone eliminated 25% of errors. For example, users attempting to 'create a presentation' (not a supported document type) now get a helpful redirect message instead of a model error.",
    "2. Context window management: The model was occasionally receiving truncated context, leading to hallucinated responses. Jake's team implemented a sliding window approach that ensures the model always receives complete context for the current document or task.",
    "3. Response validation: A post-processing step that checks model output against a schema before presenting it to the user. Malformed responses are caught and the user sees a 'please try again' message rather than a broken UI element.",
    "",
    "Production deploy is planned for December 15. Jake estimates the production rate will settle at 5.5-6.0%, down from 7.2%. The remaining improvements to reach the <3% target will require model fine-tuning, which is planned for Q1 2026.",
    "",
    "Sarah asked about the Smart Alerts improvement timeline. Jake confirmed that Smart Alerts shares the same NLP pipeline as AI Copilot, so the input validation and response validation improvements will also benefit Smart Alerts. He expects the Smart Alerts error rate to drop from 7.4% to approximately 6.0% with the December 15 deploy.",
    "",
    "### Support-Churn Correlation (Owner: Priya Patel)",
    "",
    "Priya completed the correlation analysis and presented the findings. The analysis covered all 500 accounts, 600 churn events, and approximately 2,000 support tickets across 2024-2025.",
    "",
    "Key findings:",
    "- Accounts with 3+ urgent tickets in a quarter have 4x higher churn rate. This is the single strongest predictor of churn in our data.",
    "- Accounts with CSAT below 3.0 (on the 1-5 scale) in their most recent ticket have 3.2x higher churn rate.",
    "- Accounts with declining feature usage (>30% drop over 2 months) have 2.8x higher churn rate.",
    "- The combination of high urgent tickets + declining usage correctly identified 78% of Q4 churned accounts 30 days before the churn event. False positive rate: 15%.",
    "",
    "Priya noted that these findings are now incorporated into the Customer Health Score Framework document, which she shared with Sarah on November 28 for review. The framework proposes a composite score (0-100) with four components: feature engagement (40% weight), support health (25%), usage trend (20%), and contract health (15%).",
    "",
    "Sarah confirmed she has reviewed the framework and supports moving to implementation in Q1 2026. She will include it in the Churn Reduction Initiative Proposal.",
    "",
    "### AI Search GA Plan (Owner: Jake Morrison)",
    "",
    "Jake provided a detailed status update on the AI Search GA launch:",
    "",
    "- Feature freeze: Complete as of November 20. No new features will be added before GA.",
    "- Documentation: 80% complete. The user guide, admin configuration guide, and API reference are written. The migration guide for beta users (explaining what changes in the GA version) is in draft.",
    "- Load testing: In progress. Current results show the system handles 8,000 queries/hour without degradation. The target is 10,000 queries/hour. Jake's infrastructure team is tuning the embedding cache to close the gap.",
    "- Rollback procedure: Documented. If a critical issue is found post-launch, the system can revert to the beta version within 15 minutes using a feature flag.",
    "- Monitoring: A dedicated GA monitoring dashboard is live, tracking error rate, latency (p50, p95, p99), query volume, and user satisfaction signals.",
    "",
    "Launch date confirmed: January 15, 2026. Li Wei will coordinate the in-app announcement, Jen Nakamura will handle the blog post and email campaign, and David Kim's sales team will use the GA launch in competitive deals against AcmeSaaS.",
    "",
    "### AI Copilot Usability Study (Owner: Li Wei)",
    "",
    "Li Wei presented the full findings from her 8-interview usability study, conducted between November 5-12 with Enterprise users across DevTools (3), FinTech (2), Cybersecurity (2), and HealthTech (1) verticals.",
    "",
    "Key finding: 40% of AI Copilot errors are users attempting unsupported operations. The breakdown of error causes:",
    "- 40% unsupported operations (user asks for something AI Copilot cannot do)",
